<plot>This Screenliner short shows how the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) looks at drug claims that may be fraudulent. In this case, a product called "Elixirex" is advertised as a cure-all for almost any ailment, including arthritis, rheumatism, and diabetes. After a diabetes patient dies following use of Elixirex, FDA inspectors start their investigation.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?431389</url></doc>
